            <p>North Bay is a four-hour drive from Toronto — and for Chinese-Canadian families there facing divorce or family breakdown, finding a Mandarin-speaking family lawyer is an acute challenge. Miao He (何淼) serves North Bay clients <strong>entirely by Zoom and phone</strong>. No travel required. Court appearances at the Superior Court of Justice — North Bay Courthouse are handled by Miao He when needed, with travel costs disclosed in advance. LSO #83315K · China Bar Association Licensed.</p>
          </div>

          <h2>Full Family Law Service — Remotely</h2>
          <p>North Bay's distance from major urban centres does not have to mean lower quality legal service. Ontario's family law courts have embraced remote proceedings since 2020, and the majority of family law work — consultation, document preparation, strategy, Separation Agreement drafting — has always been paper and communication based. For North Bay clients, here is what the process looks like with Miao He.</p>

          <h3>Zoom Consultations: Starting Your Case from North Bay</h3>
          <p>The initial consultation, case assessment, document review, and ongoing strategy discussions all happen by Zoom. Miao He speaks Mandarin directly — no interpreter costs, no translation risk. You can share documents on screen, ask questions freely, and get clear answers in your own language. Most North Bay clients complete the bulk of their matter without leaving their home.</p>

          <h3>Separation Agreements: The Most Efficient Path for North Bay Families</h3>
          <p>If both spouses are willing to negotiate, a Separation Agreement is the most efficient resolution — and it can be completed entirely by Zoom. Miao He drafts the agreement covering property division, support, and parenting arrangements, reviews it with each client to ensure full understanding, and facilitates signing. This avoids court entirely and is often the right approach for North Bay families who want closure without a long litigation process.</p>

          <h3>Divorce Litigation: When Court is Necessary</h3>
          <p>When matters cannot be resolved by agreement, Miao He litigates. Court appearances at the Superior Court of Justice — North Bay Courthouse (360 Plouffe Street) are handled by Miao He in person when required. Many procedural appearances can be conducted by Zoom under Ontario's post-2020 court practices. Travel to North Bay for in-person hearings is done as needed, with costs disclosed in advance.</p>

          <h3>Child Custody and Northern Ontario Realities</h3>
          <p>Northern Ontario custody cases often involve geographic realities that don't arise in the GTA — long distances between parents, limited transportation infrastructure, and school and activity schedules that reflect a different way of life. Miao He builds Parenting Plans that account for these realities, with specific provisions that reduce ambiguity and future disputes.</p>

          <div class="qa-block">
            <h3>Q: Can I handle my entire divorce remotely from North Bay?</h3>
            <p>A: Yes. All consultations, documents, and drafting are handled by Zoom. Court appearances are handled by Miao He. Most North Bay clients complete their matter without visiting the Markham office. Call 647-930-6688.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="qa-block">
            <h3>Q: My spouse has moved to Toronto. Do we divorce in North Bay or Toronto?</h3>
            <p>A: Jurisdiction depends on ordinary residence — either location in Ontario can work. Miao He can advise on the most practical court to file in based on your circumstances. Call 647-930-6688.</p>
          </div>

